<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_tab_settings">3.1. Tab: Settings</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Settings</strong> tab is automatically opened when a category is opened.</p>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%;">
<col style="width: 50%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Setting</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Type</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select <strong>Item</strong>, <strong>Content</strong> or <strong>Container</strong>.<br>
In the directory tree, categories of the type <strong>Item</strong> are blue. Categories of the type <strong>Content</strong> are yellow and categories of the type <strong>Container</strong> are red.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Name</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter a name for the category.<br>
You can re-use category names as long as they are used in different categories or on different levels. Within one category, however, the names may only be used once per level. This makes it possible to save different meta descriptions etc. for categories with the same name.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Tags</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the tags that match the category. Suggestions are automatically displayed while you type. Tags show that a category relates to a specific topic. Go to <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/tags"><strong>Settings » Basic settings » Tags</strong></a> to create tags.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>URL name</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter a name that should be used for the URL.<br>
The name will automatically be used as the URL name when the category is crated. However, the URL name can still be changed here. The automatic URL will not be indexed at first because a client is not selected when the category is created.<br>
You can re-use URL names as long as they are used in different categories or on different levels. Within one category, however, the URL names may only be used once per level.<br>
<em><strong>Important:</strong></em> Only use <strong>ASCII code</strong>. This is because the URL name may not contain special characters. The following character strings may not be used as prefixes to URL names: a-, b-, c-, f-, fa-, p-, t-. These prefixes will be removed automatically if entered. For instance, a-class will be changed to class automatically. However, the URL name aclass can be used for a category named A-class.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>URL</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>The category URL will be displayed.<br>
It is automatically created and entered. It includes the complete path, i.e. the domain, the category levels and the URL name.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Canonical</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter the URL of the category that contains the same content. This will avoid <strong>duplicate content</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Short description</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter a short description of the category. Template variables are used to insert the short description into the store’s design.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Position</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter a number to specify which order the categories and subcategories should be displayed in on the same level. Go to <strong><a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/item-layouts">Settings » Client (store) » Standard » Item layouts » Basic settings</a></strong> to specify the pages' sorting order. Pages are sorted in ascending position order by default.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> Count by tens when creating position numbers. This will allow you to easily add new categories in between.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Client (store)</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select one, several or all of the clients. The category will then be available in these clients.<br>
If a client is activated for a subcategory but it was not yet activated for the category above it, then the parent category will automatically be activated as well. If other clients are already activated for parent categories, then the new client will be activated as well. Previously selected clients continue to be activated.<br>
<strong>Apply visibility to subcategories</strong><br>
This option will only be displayed if subcategories exist.<br>
Place a check mark to apply the category’s client visibility to all of its subcategories. This function is only activated until the next time you save the category. This means that you have to place the check mark again every time you want to apply a category’s visibility to its subcategories.<br>
If a visibility is removed (i.e. a check mark is removed from any of the clients and the category is saved), then this will be applied to the subcategories even if the function is not activated.<br>
If a visibility is added, then this visibility will also automatically be set for any parent categories.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Meta title</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter a name. This name will be displayed as the title of a tab in the web browser and as a search result in search engines.<br>
If you leave this field blank, the Name will be used as the title.<br>
Pay attention to the length of the title. Short titles are better for tabs. Longer titles will be cut off after a certain length. (Standard value up to 50 characters)</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Meta description</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter a meta description. This will be analyzed by search engines. As such, it is especially important for the homepage. The meta description should contain the most important content in one sentence. (Standard value up to 140 characters)</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Meta keywords</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter concrete keywords that users would likely enter into search engines.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Sitemap</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Choose between <strong>Display</strong> and <strong>Do not display</strong>.<br>
<strong>Display</strong> = Category will be included in the sitemap.<br>
<strong>Do not display</strong> = Category will not be included in the sitemap.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Robots</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Choose between <strong>all</strong>, <strong>index</strong>, <strong>nofollow</strong>, <strong>noindex</strong> and <strong>nofollow, noindex</strong>. Values from the meta element Robots are analyzed by Web crawlers. These values tell the crawler what it should do with this page and with the links on this page.<br>
<strong>all</strong> = Include this category in the search engine index and follow the links on the page.<br>
<strong>index</strong> = Include in the search engine index.<br>
<strong>nofollow</strong> = Do not follow the links on the page.<br>
<strong>noindex</strong> = Do not include in the search engine index.<br>
<strong>nofollow, noindex</strong> = Do not follow the links and do not include the category in the search engine index.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Template page</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a template. The template that is selected here provides the framework for the category. This option is not available for categories of the type <strong>Container</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Template list</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a template. The template determines what the category overview will look like for the current category. The option is only available for <strong>categories of the type item</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Template product</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a template. The template determines the appearance of the single item design for this category. The option is only available for <strong>categories of the type item</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Full text search</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Choose between <strong>Yes</strong> and <strong>No</strong>.<br>
<strong>Yes</strong> = Complete text will be searched.<br>
<strong>No</strong> = Text will not be completely searched.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>in link list</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Choose between <strong>Display</strong> and <strong>Do not display</strong>.<br>
<strong>Display</strong> = Category will be displayed in the store’s navigation.<br>
<strong>Do not display</strong> = Category will not be displayed in the store’s navigation.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Visible</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Choose between <strong>Public</strong> and <strong>After login</strong>.<br>
<strong>Public</strong> = Category is visible to all visitors of the online store.<br>
<strong>After login</strong> = Category and all of its subcategories are only visible to visitors of the online store that have logged in. Visitors that are not logged in will be redirected to the login page.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Elmar category</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select an Elmar category.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Translate template variables and template functions</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Choose between <strong>Yes</strong>, <strong>No</strong> and <strong>Template variables and template functions for links only</strong>.<br>
<strong>Yes</strong> = All template variables and template functions will be translated.<br>
<strong>Template variables and template functions for links only</strong> = Only template variables and template functions for links will be translated.<br>
<strong>No</strong> = No template variables and template functions will be translated.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
